Integument:
Prodorsum, notogaster, venter, anal and genital plates, and mentum micropunctate. Coxisternum, pedotectum I and pteromorph with fine striae forming weakly reticulate pattern (
Figs 6F, G
), lamella laterally with strong striae, with textured pattern of ridges medially (
Figs 6F
, 
14D
). Rostrum with textured pattern of ridges (
Fig. 6E
).

Lateral region of podosoma
: Genal tooth broad, subrectangular, with dens ventrodistally, with longitudinal ridge ventrolaterally (
Figs 6E
, 
7B
). Tutorium about 175 µm long, of which cusp about 86 µm long, rectangular; distal margin with 6–10 dentes along anterodorsal and distal margin (
Fig. 7B
). Custodium about 56 µm long, tapered (
Fig. 28B
). Porose area Al about 11 µm in diameter.
